Individuals who had been diagnosed with T2DM treating with diet/exercise or Metformin 850 mg or Pioglitazone 30mg once daily, and were attending Outdoor Patient Department (OPD) of BIRDEM for consultation were approached by the researcher and invited to participate in the study.

 The patients were diagnosed already and registered in BIRDEM.

 T2DM was ascertained based on World Health Organization recommended criteria two repeated measures of fasting (plasma glucose 7.

