 Patient Preparation: I.

Written informed consent was obtained from all participants before study entry.

 Patients were instructed to follow adhere to a disease- and weight-orientated diet throughout the study as before.

 II.

Each case history was documented in the case report form.

 The study was approved by the National Medical Ethics Review Boards (NMERB) of Bangladesh Medical Research Council (BMRC).

The investigations were carried out in accordance with the principles of the Declaration of Helsinki as revised in 2000.

 4.

 Treatment: The patients were to receive treatment pioglitazone tablet 001 (30mg once per day) for 3 months followed by one month "metformin wash-out period", then to the alternative treatment regimen for further 3 months with metformin tablet 002 (850mg once per day).

 The drugs were supplied by the Aristopharma Pharmaceutical Ltd.

